<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT July 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov said that
the further development of the Russia-China strategic and
cooperative partnership is crucial for safeguarding world security
and stability.
</P>
<P>
Primakov made the statement here Thursday at a press conference
after meeting with Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
(China-Russia-FM-Press Conference)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUNMING -- Farmers in China's northwestern Yunnan Province last
weekend discovered bodies on a snow-covered mountain which are
believed to be the remains of the mountaineers missing in a
Sino-Japanese joint expedition in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The bodies were found on a glacier on Mt. Meili 4,000 meters
above sea level in Deqin County. The China Mountaineering
Association and the Yunnan Provincial Sports Commission have
instructed to keep the bodies at the site intact for further
confirmation. (China-Mountaineer Remains-Found)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING) -- China welcomed Thursday the vote by the U.S. House
of Representatives approving President Bill Clinton's decision to
maintain normal trade relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi
Guangshen that reciprocal arrangement is conducive to the normal
development of bilateral trade. (China-US-Trade Vote)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- President Aslan Maskhadov of Russia's breakaway
republic of Chechnya survived an assassination attempt Thursday
morning. He was only slightly injured.
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov was riding in a car on the way to his working
residence when a bomb-loaded UAZ car exploded in the area of
Beryozki bus station.
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov's armored car caught fire but he managed to jump out
and sustained minor knee injury. (Russia-Chechnya-Maskhadov)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- The convicted Tehran mayor, Gholamhussein Karbaschi,
would appeal against the court verdict, Karbaschi's lawyer Bahman
Keshavarz announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Keshavarz said that the court decision did not come as a
surprise and the defense team had "expected such a verdict," the
official news agency IRNA reported. (Iran-Mayor-Verdict) 
</P>
</TEXT>
