<HEADLINE> 3 NPC Vice-Chairmen Visit Exhibition for Grand National Theater </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Zou Jiahua, He Luli and Jiang
Zhenghua, all vice-chairmen of the Standing Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), have visited an
exhibition of possible designs for the planned Grand National
Theater.
</P>
<P>
All 44 design plans, outlining both external and internal
features of the theater, are on display at the exhibit which
opened on July 19.
</P>
<P>
The plans were submitted by 20 design institutes from nine
foreign countries including the United States, Germany, Japan,
Canada, and France, and 16 design institutes from China's interior
areas and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Three proposed designs will be nominated from the 44 now being
shown by the appraisal committee for design plans of the Grand
National Theater.
</P>
<P>
The theater's builders will decide from among the three
finalists which design institute will be awarded the project.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
