<HEADLINE> France Assists China's Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- France is to donate 700,000 francs
(117,000 U.S. dollars) in humanitarian aid to flood victims  in
China, the French Foreign Ministry announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The fund, provided by the French government, will be run by the
French humanitarian group, Medecins sans Frontieres, said the
Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux. 
</P>
