<HEADLINE> Germany's Inflation Remains Low in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Germany's inflation remained low at
0.9 percent in July, showed provisional figures issued by the
Federal Statistics Office in Wiesbaden Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The July year-on-year figure was based on information collected
from four key federal states. Full national figures, which are to
be released later, are almost always identical.
</P>
<P>
The country's moderate inflation was attributed to low oil
prices. Fuel oil price went 13 percent cheaper than a year before
and motor fuel, 3 percent lower. 
</P>
</TEXT>
