<HEADLINE> Nine Others Detained by Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Festina cycling team leader Richard
Virenque, world champion Laurent Borchard and seven other riders
of the Festina Tour de France team were detained for questioning
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
They had arrived together at police headquarters in the
southeastern city Lyon to be interrogated by police probing doping
scandals on the tour.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Thursday, three Festina officials were detained.
They are sports director Miguel Martinez, his assistant Michel
Gros and maintenance and communications manager Joel Chabrion.
</P>
