<HEADLINE> Becker Sets up Duel with Rios </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker set up a quarterfinal
duel with top seed Marcelo Rios after beating Spain's Felix
Mantilla 7-6 (7-2), 7-5 on in the third round of the Mercedes Cup
on Thursday in Stuttgart.
</P>
<P>
Rios, who earlier entered the quarter-finals by defeating
German Hendrik Dreekmann 6-3, 6-4, has to beat the 30-year-old
Becker to take back the world No.1 ranking from Pete Sampras.
</P>
<P>
The semi-retired Becker, 81st in the world, showed the fighting
qualities to take a marathon 12th game of the opening set, and
proceeded to dominate the second set for the final win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
