<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Shows Concerns to Flood Situation in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji made a
phone-call this evening, on behalf of the Party Central Committee
and the State Council, to Governor Yang Zhengwu of Hunan Province
to show concern over local flood situation.
</P>
<P>
He also extended cordial regards to officials and people as
well as officers and men of the People's Liberation Army and armed
police.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu urged both leading bodies and individuals in the
locality to spare no effort to safeguard the people's life and
properties as well as major cities and key infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Since July 20, heavy or torrential rains, with a total rainfall
of more than 600 mm, have caused severe floods in western and
northwestern Hunan, with water levels of local rivers exceeding
the warning line at all measuring points.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than three million people in 15 counties in
northwestern Hunan have been suffering from floods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
