<HEADLINE> Cellular Phone System to Be Operational in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The first cellular phones in
Swaziland will be in operation when the kingdom is celebrating
its 30th independence anniversary on September 8, a senior
official said in Mbabane, Swaziland Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The cellular phone system would be launched at an ideal time
when thousands of foreign visitors, including potential
investors, would be in the kingdom for the celebrations, Swazi
Tourism and Communications Minister Musa Nkambule said.
</P>
<P>
Mobile Telephone Network was awarded the 10-year contract to
install and operate the system in Swaziland.
</P>
<P>
Bordering with South Africa, Swaziland, with a population of
one million, has relatively easy access to international
telecommunication. 
</P>
</TEXT>
