<HEADLINE> UNDP Goodwill Ambassador on 1st Trip to Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Internationally acclaimed
actor and long-time social activist Danny Glover completed
Thursday his first mission to Namibia and South Africa as goodwill
ambassador of the United Nations Development Program (UNDP)
</P>
<P>
"This position gives me not only the opportunity to make a
statement about what needs to be done in the world, but also to
understand how people take what are often limited resources to
build and sustain their community," Glover, who was appointed as
UNDP's first goodwill ambassador last March, told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"The purpose of my trip was to witness the kind of impact
programs sponsored by UNDP are having on the ground and within the
national context in which they operate," he said.
</P>
<P>
"There are stories of hope in Namibia and South Africa. I saw
individuals successfully working collectively from the grassroots
level to the policy level to eradicate poverty in their community
and country. Their determination and hard work made me even more
determined to use my position as UNDP goodwill ambassador to tell
the world that they just need the international community to
assist them with additional human and financial resources," Glover
said.
</P>
<P>
"In both Namibia and South Africa, it is truly a miracle that
so much is being done effectively in such short periods of time.
These are the stories of hope that are alive and well around the
world but never appeared in the media," he added. 
</P>
