<HEADLINE> UK Company Clones Transgenic Lambs Carrying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- UK's PPL Therapeutics Plc announced
Thursday that it had cloned new transgenic lambs carrying the
human protein extra cellular superoxide dismutase (EC SOD).
</P>
<P>
The Lambs, born at PPL's farm in Scotland, were developed from
an frozen somatic cell line using nuclear transfer technology, a
technique used by PPL and UK's Roslin Institute to produce Dolly
the sheep.
</P>
<P>
The frozen fetal fibroblast cells, imported from PPL's sheep
farm in New Zealand, were genetically modified to include the
human EC SOD gene and then transferred to unfertilized eggs, the
company said.
</P>
<P>
PPL is one of the world's leading companies in the production
of human proteins in the milk of transgenic sheep and cattle for
therapeutic and nutritional use.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
