<HEADLINE> Top French Daily Calls for Stop of '98 Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- France's top daily Le Monde Friday
called for an end to the Tour de France 1998 cycling tournament,
plagued by widespread doping scandals.
</P>
<P>
"The Tour de France is finished. To say more exactly it has
never begun. Once for all, the show should not go on,,'' said Le
Monde in an editorial which rapped the doping scandals that broke
out one after another.
</P>
<P>
It blamed the organizers for pretending not to see "the strange
manners of the cyclists and the terrible affects of the doping."
</P>
<P>
"It is up to them to prevent the drowning of this competition
and to save and relaunch on good basis this prestigious match
between all," it said.
</P>
<P>
At least two professional cycling teams have been discovered to
have systematically resorted to drugs during this year's Tour de
France, which is still in the middle of its way.
</P>
<P>
"The cyclists should put their feet on the land and go for
examination of conscience. Police and justice should work to
shelter from pressure. Organizers, federal officials, medical
authorities and public powers should open debate they refused for
years out of fear or interests," said the daily.
</P>
<P>
It pointed out that the Tour de France should either face the
truth or die out completely. 
</P>
