<HEADLINE> Rios Stays on Course for World Numble One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Marcelo Rios moved a step
closer to taking back the world No.1 ranking when he routed crowd
favourite Boris Becker 6-2, 6-0 on Friday and moved into the
semi-finals of the Mercedes Cup in Stuttgart.
</P>
<P>
If Rios beats his next opponent Karol Kucera of Slovakia, the
22-year-old Chilean will replace Peter Sampras as the new World
number one.
</P>
<P>
Kucera reached the last four with a 6-4, 6-4 victory against
Bohdan Ulihrach.
</P>
<P>
French Open winner Carlos Moya had to work hard to dismiss
qualifier Fernando Vicente of Spain 3-6, 6-3, 6-2 in another
quarter-final.
</P>
<P>
Moya will await an opponent from Friday's final quarter-final
between former French Open title holder Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil
and Spaniard Albert Costa. 
</P>
