<HEADLINE> French Police Arrest Suspected Algerian Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Agents of the French secret police
Direction de la Surveillance du Territoire (DST) have arrested
four suspected members of the Algerian terrorist group Takfir Wall
Hijra, French judicial sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Takfir Wall Hijra is a dissident movement of the Algerian
terrorist group Armed Islamic Group (GIA).
</P>
<P>
The four suspected terrorists, who were armed when arrested
last Saturday, have been charged with association with malfeasance
in relation with a terrorist enterprise, and detained by Judge
Jean-Francois Ricard of a Paris investigation court.
</P>
<P>
All four are Algerian nationals and suspected of being
involved in running a support network for terrorists in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Police are trying to establish whether they were connected with
another group of Islamic militants of the GIA arrested in May by
the Italian security service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
