<HEADLINE> Nokia Sales, Profits Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 24 (Xinhua) - Sales and profits of Nokia
increased by 41 percent and 75 percent respectively in the second
quarter of the year, compared with the first quarter, the company
said in its quarterly report Friday.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunications equipment company said sales reached
18.42 billion Finnish marks (3.35 billion U.S. dollars) while
profit stood at 3.35 billion marks (609 million dollars) between
April and June.
</P>
<P>
During the period, sales of telecommunications equipment and
mobile phones rose by up 45 percent and 50 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Company president Jorma Ollila attributed the strong growth to
many factors, including consolidation of its market, notably the
U.S. market and a creative and devoted workforce.
</P>
<P>
Nokia is among the three biggest mobile phone suppliers in the
world with a market share of 21 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
