<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches Web Site for SAARC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colombo, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Foreign Ministry has
launched its own web site to provide information about the 10th
summit of the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation
(SAARC), according to a press release of the Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The new site will be accessible through www.lanka.net/fm, said
the press release circulated at a press conference by Sri Lankan
Foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar here Friday.
</P>
<P>
A special feature of this site will be the incorporation of a
section devoted to the 10th SAARC summit, which will be kept
updated throughout the period Sri Lanka holds the chair of the
SAARC, providing the world with a window on the activities of the
organization.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka will take over the chair of the SAARC from the
Maldives at the 10th summit scheduled to be held here from July 29
to 31.
</P>
<P>
This site, designed by the Foreign Ministry in collaboration
with the Institute of Computer Technology of the University of
Colombo and Lanka Internet Services Ltd., will be hosted on the
Lanka Internet Web Server, known as the "Sri Lanka Web Server".
</P>
<P>
The special section in the web site relating to the 10th SAARC
summit will provide background information on the SAARC and its
member countries, declarations from the previous summits, the
program, statements, press releases and finally the declaration
emanating from the Colombo summit.
</P>
<P>
A "live stream broadcast" of the opening and closing sessions
and the press conference of the SAARC summit and a video summary
of the conference related activities on each day will also be made
available to international browses at the same address. 
</P>
</TEXT>
