<HEADLINE> Indonesian House Passes Anti-Torture Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian House of
Representatives (DPR) Friday approved a bill on the Convention
Against Torture and Cruel, Inhuman or Degrading Treatment or
Punishment.
</P>
<P>
The approval was given based on the final statements by the
four House factions at a plenary session led by Deputy House
Speaker Hari Sabarno here.
</P>
<P>
"Based on reports on the outcome of debates about the Bill
against Torture in Commission I and the approvals expressed by the
four House factions, the House hereby passes the bill and will
convey it to the President for its promulgation as a law," Sabarno
said.
</P>
<P>
The bill against torture was forwarded by House members'
themselves using the House's right to initiate legislation on any
topic of their choice. It was the first time in more than 30 years
for the DPR to use its right to propose a bill. 
</P>
