<HEADLINE> Foreign Visitors to South Africa Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The number of overseas
visitors to South Africa increased by 9.7 percent in December
1997, compared with that of the same period in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The November 1997 figure was 6.4 percent up on that of the
previous year, according to a latest survey by the country's
Central Statistical Service.
</P>
<P>
In November 1977, 20.1 percent of visitors were from the
United Kingdom, making it the leading country of origin for
overseas visitors. It was followed by Germany (19.3 percent),
the United States (8.4), the Netherlands (6.3), France
(5.6) and Australia (3.2).
</P>
<P>
The number of travelers to South Africa from other parts of
Africa decreased by 3.3 percent in November 1997 compared with
the same period in the previous year, the survey showed. 
</P>
