<HEADLINE> Shenyang-Shanhaiguan Railway Resumes Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Shenshan Railway, which runs
from the city of Shenyang in northeastern Liaoning Province to
Shanhaiguan Pass in north China's Hebei Province, resumed services
today after seven hours' rush repairs done to damaged tracks
caused by torrential rains.
</P>
<P>
The rail line through the western part of Liaoning is a vital
communications link connecting northeast China with inland
provinces. Train service was suspended at 7:30 a.m. today because
of landslides and devastating floods caused by very heavy rainfall.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 1,000 railway workers of the Shenyang Railway
Administration Bureau and its branch office in Jinzhou City were
aroused today to bring the damaged railway track back into
service.  
</P>
