<HEADLINE> Chongqing Accelerates Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction of an expressway
commenced today in the southwest China municipality of Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The 87-km section of the Chongqing-Guizhou Expressway, funded
with loans from the Asian Development Bank, is part of an
ambitious road construction program in Chongqing, China's largest
municipality with a population of over 30 million people.
</P>
<P>
The mountainous city, which is divided by several major rivers,
including the Yangtze and the Jialing, has always faced a
difficult situation in terms of highway construction.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, related difficulties have failed to frighten
developers concerned with the city's future.
</P>
<P>
The four expressways currently under construction in the
municipality will link its major cities and counties.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has not only used loans of international
financial institutions and foreign governments, but also allowed
overseas investors to participate in highway construction.
</P>
<P>
Five major highway bridges over the Yangtze River were
completed during 1998. Substantial progress has also been recorded
in the construction of roads leading the municipality to the
massive Three Gorges Water Conservancy Project.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has decided to invest some 21.6 billion
yuan (2.6 billion US dollars) over the next five years in the
construction of a new expressway network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
