<HEADLINE> Cruyff Is Dutch People's Favorite for Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Johan Cruyff is the Dutch
people's best choice to succeed Guus Hiddink as the national
soccer team coach, said a survey published Friday in Amsterdam,
the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
One in three people interviewed for the poll picked Cruyff,
who captained the Dutch ``Clockwork Orange'' team that lost the
1974 World Cup final to West Germany, according to reports from
Amsterdam.
</P>
<P>
Cruyff, who has coached Ajax Amsterdam and Spanish giant
Barcelona, is currently working as a television soccer analyst.
</P>
<P>
Hiddink was hired as coach by Real Madrid after guiding the
Netherlands to a semifinal berth in the World Cup finals in France
and the Dutch soccer association is hunting for a successor,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
The man regarded by the Dutch media as favorite for the job,
former Glasgow Celtic manager Wim Jansen, was picked by just 12
percent of the 1,000 people interviewed for the poll by market
research company NIPO.
</P>
<P>
Jansen and Cruyff are teammates in the 1974 World Cup.
</P>
