<HEADLINE> Chinese Swimmers Receive Two-year Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Swimming world governing body FINA
on Friday announced a two-year ban for four Chinese swimmers
committing drug offences to prevent them from all competition.
</P>
<P>
The four swimmers are Zhang Yi, Wang Wei, Wang Luna and Cai
Huijue. They all tested positive for the steroid masking agent
triamterene at the World Championships in Perth, Australia in
January.
</P>
<P>
FINA also said the suspension would go into force immediately.
A temporary ban from 14 January to 25 April will be deducted from
the two-year total.
</P>
<P>
But Charles Duan, the Chinese lawyer representing the four,
said after Friday's hearing that the four will fight the ban and
appeal the decision at Lausanne's Tribunal of Sport. 
