<HEADLINE> Trade Between S. Africa, Argentina Shoots up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Trade between South Africa
and Argentina rose to 404.6 million U.S. Dollars last year, local
daily Business Report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Argentine exports increased by 22 percent to 295.4 million
U.S. Dollars and imports from South Africa were 109.1 million
Dollars, the Argentine embassy was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
South Africa was the 21st export destination for Argentina
last year. Brazil, the United States and Chile remain its
dominate export markets. Argentina is South Africa's 27th largest
export market.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela, who is presently
visiting Argentina, has signed bilateral agreements in Buenos
Aires, on drug traffic control and on reciprocal investment
promotion and protection to encourage greater investment flows
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum of understanding on political consultations and
an accord on visa exemption for South African passport holders
were also signed.  
