<HEADLINE> Gansu Introduces Property Rights Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- At a conference here today, 510
property rights transfer projects in northwest China's Gansu
Province were introduced.
</P>
<P>
According to Deng Chengcheng, a provincial official in charge
of property rights, the transfer of these rights can be very
flexible, whether through merger, joint investment, shareholding,
or reorganization.
</P>
<P>
Of the 510 projects, with a total value of 8.6 billion yuan,
