The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- A veto of the Republican managed-care bill was threatened by
President Bill Clinton. He said it lacks protection such as
guaranteed access to specialists and a ban on financial
arrangements that push doctors to limit care. House leaders sought
moderates' support before a possible vote Friday.
</P>
<P>
USA Today:
</P>
<P>
-- In a move to stop an unregulated, fast growing, mostly
offshore business, the Senate voted 90-10 Thursday to pull the
plug on most forms of Internet gambling. 
</P>
