<TEXT>
<P>
Joyner-Kersee, the 36-year-old world's greatest all-round woman
athlete, competes for the last time on Saturday in a long jump at
an International Amateur Athletic (IAAF) Grand Prix meeting in
Edwardsville, near East St Louis, Illinois.
</P>
<P>
In her 18-year career, she has won three Olympic gold medals --
two in the heptathlon and one in the long jump -- set world
records and won world titles.
