<HEADLINE> China Confident of Realizing 1998 Trade Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- China is both confident and fully
capable of achieving its goal of a 345 billion U.S. dollar trade
volume for 1998, according to Hu Zhaoqing, spokesman for the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks at today's press conference and noted that
China faces major challenges in trade during the second half of
the year due to the worsening financial turmoil in Asia.
</P>
<P>
However, the growing global economy and good domestic economic
environment will enable China to defy all odds and fulfill all
tasks, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Intensified efforts will be made to implement the
market diversification strategy and epitomize the export
structure. Moreover, he added, China will require enterprises to
further develop their capacities, reduce costs and expenditures,
take emergency measures to cope with changing situation and reduce
market risks.
</P>
<P>
China's total import-export volume hit 325 billion U.S. dollars
last year, with year-on-year growth of 12.1 percent. The trade
volume of the first half of 1997 jumped 13 percent to 143.8
billion US dollars, with the volume for the first half of this
year growing by 5.2 percent to 151.4 billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
