<HEADLINE> Bank of China Pledges Loans for Steel Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) plans to
grant services valued at two billion yuan (242 million US dollars)
to the Handan Steel Group Ltd in Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of the bank's effort to support key
enterprises with a good profit-making records and credit ratings.
</P>
<P>
The cooperative agreement signed today between the bank and the
company calls for the BOC to offer the latter wide-ranging
fund-raising services, as well as other services related to
settlements, consulting and funds management.
</P>
<P>
The BOC inked similar agreements with a number of large
enterprises in the January-June period, including the Konka Group,
Hainan Airlines and Xiamen Airlines. The agreements called for the
bank to provide funds totalling 42 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Over the past seven years, Handan steel group, which has total
assets of 15 billion yuan and annual steel output of three million
tons, has expanded into the nation's second largest steel producer
in terms pretax profits.
</P>
<P>
The group produced 2.55 million tons of steel in 1997, with
sales income of 5.4 billion yuan and pretax profits of 850 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Handan's goal is to produce five million tons of steel and earn
annual net profits of two billion yuan by the year 2005. 
</P>
