50 cents to close at 19.30 Singapore dollars. UOB shed 20 cents to
end at 5.50 Singapore dollars. BATS was down 16 cents to finish at
3.60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the merger of DBS Bank and POSBank stirred up
speculative fever on the market Friday.
</P>
<P>
Bank shares surged in late afternoon as traders pushed up the
shares on expectations of more mergers, they said.
</P>
