<HEADLINE> Suzhou Connected with U.N. Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, July 24 (Xinhua) -- This well-known tourist city in
east China's Jiangsu Province was connected today with the Technology
and Information Promotion System (TIPS), a global technological and
trade information network operated by the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The "Suzhou Central Station" of the TIPS China branch opened in
Suzhou City today, through which the city can promote foreign
trade and lure more overseas investments by fully utilizing the
information resources of the U.N..
</P>
<P>
The station can also help the city publicize technological,
economic, and trade information at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
China joined the global information network as a member state
in 1985. The network was established jointly by the United Nations
Development Program and the United Nations Fund for Science and
Technology Development, and has proved to be effective in
promoting both foreign trade and exchanges of technological,
economic and trade information among some 160 member
states. 
</P>
