<HEADLINE> Mongolian Government Dismissed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Great Hural (parliament) of
Mongolia Friday dismissed Prime Minister Tsakhya Elbegdorj's
government after a voting with 42 for and 33 against the motion,
said the information office of the Great Hural.
</P>
<P>
The parliamentary group of the Mongolian People's Revolutionary
Party (MPRP) on July 10 submitted a bill to the Great Hural,
urging the government to resign.
</P>
<P>
They believed that the government's decision in May to merge the
state-owned Renovation Bank into the private Golomt Bank not only
violated the country's constitution and laws but also brought
threat to national economic security and financial policies.
</P>
<P>
MPRP MPs have since then boycotted Great Hural meetings,
paralyzing the parliament for more than 50 days.
</P>
<P>
On July 10, the government took some compromising steps by
making some amendments to the decision, but the MPRP members
rejected them and insisted on the government's resignation.
</P>
<P>
President Nachagyn Bagabandy said Friday that in order to
prevent social instability he would exercise his right as
president to dismiss the parliament and the government, if the
Great Hural could not solve the dispute on the merger.
</P>
<P>
The current cabinet, which was formed in April, is the
shortest-lived in Mongolia's history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
