<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Remains Sluggish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market continued
to be sluggish for the second week in last week, a market report
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO), showed the CISCO All-Share Index
closed on Thursday at 426 points, with virtually no deviation
on the week.
</P>
<P>
The investment activity was slightly lower compared to last
week, and the daily average volume of transactions for this week
was estimated at 938,000 Cyprus pounds (about 1,876,000
U.S. dollars) compared to 1 million Cyprus pounds (about 2 million
dollars) the week before.
</P>
<P>
The review expected the year 1998 will be an active one for
the primary market, especially following the passing on July 2 by
the House of Representatives, of tax incentives for newly listed
public companies on the stock market.
</P>
<P>
The total weekly volume of transactions declined to 4.7
million Cyprus pounds (about 9.4 million dollars), from 5.6
million Cyprus pounds (about 11.2 million dollars) the week
before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
