<HEADLINE> Philippine President Congratulates Keizo Obuchi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
congratulated Friday Japanese Foreign Minister Keizo Obuchi who
was elected president of Japan's ruling party and is expected to
be the next prime minister of the country.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, Estrada expressed hope that Obuchi's
emergence as the successor of resigned Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto would pave the way for a further strengthening of ties
between Manila and Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi was elected president of the Liberal Democratic Party
(LDP) Friday afternoon, and actually won the party's nomination
for the prime ministership of the country. His nomination is
expected to be confirmed next week by Japan's parliament, which is
controlled by the LDP.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said he was hoping that Obuchi would favorably consider
his proposal that Japan be more open to dealings with the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
"I hope the new Japanese leader will be receptive to a
Philippine government proposal for Japan to take a more active
interest in the affairs of the ASEAN," Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines is hosting the two-day 31st annual ASEAN
Ministerial Meeting, which opened here Friday morning. The meeting
is followed by the 5th ASEAN Regional Forum and the Post
Ministerial Conference.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi, whose country is a dialogue partner of ASEAN, is
expected to arrive in Manila next week to attend the ASEAN
gathering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
