<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Makes Fight Against Crime its Priority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian government has made
the crackdown on organized crime its top social target and most
important task, according to the local press Friday.
</P>
<P>
In its National Unified Strategy against Crime, adopted last
week, the government said that it will take comprehensive measures
to reduce crime, in particular organized economic crime, so as to
wipe out the adverse effects of crime on economic reform,
financial stability and social order.
</P>
<P>
The document conceded that since 1990, the number of crime
cases has "risen drastically," hampering the country's economic
reform, draining state wealth and endangering the people's
lives. 
</P>
