vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission, met today
with General Valeri Manilov, first deputy chief of General Staff
of the Russian Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
Manilov is in Beijing to attend the second round strategy and
security consultations between the general staff headquarters of
the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that the consultation mechanism has helped enhance
understanding and strengthen friendship between the two armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China and Russian are neighbors with a long
history of friendship.
</P>
<P>
Zhang pointed out that frequent visits between top leaders have
led to the sound and steady development of Sino-Russian relations
and propelled the relationship into a new era.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that developing friendly cooperative relations
between the two countries is not only in the best interests of the
two nations, but is also of great significance in accelerating the
process of world multipolarization process and establishing a new
political and economic order based on peace, stability, justice
and fairness.
</P>
<P>
Manilov praised China for its achievements since the initiation
of reform and opening to the outside world in the early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is playing an increasingly important role in
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Manilov expressed the hope for strengthened exchanges and
cooperation between the two countries and their armed forces. He
noted that stronger relations will promote the development of the
Sino-Russian strategic cooperative partnership oriented to the
21st century.
</P>
<P>
A number of military officials, including Lieutenant General
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of General Staff of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army, attended the meeting. 
