<HEADLINE> Blaze Hits Japanese Ship in UAE Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- A huge fire has damaged some
3,000 cars aboard a Japanese cargo ship Friday at the Khalid port in
Sharja Emirate of the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
Police sources at Sharja Emirate told Xinhua by phone that the
burning ship was towed into the sea about five kilometers
from the Khalid port after the failure to control the fire.
</P>
<P>
The police source declined to reveal the extent of total
damage cause by the blaze.
</P>
<P>
The fire began Thursday evening on the ship after one of the
cars caught fire fro unknown reason. The fire immediately spread
to all the cars which were lined up in six decks.
</P>
<P>
UAE civil defense forces and fire-fighters rushed to control
the fire but failed. 
