<HEADLINE> Circular Urges Priority Battle Against Yangtze Flooding(1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Provinces and cities along the
Yangtze River should immediately introduce emergency measures and
spare no effort to secure water conservancy projects, including
dikes and dams, and battle extended flooding in the river valley.
</P>
<P>
The call came in an emergency circular issued early this
morning by the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters, which convened a meeting at midnight Thursday to
discuss the Yangtze River flood situation.
</P>
<P>
Water levels in the river valley have remained at flood stage
since late June, with torrential rains in the middle and lower
reaches since July 21 causing serious flooding in the Dongting
Lake area in Hunan Province and Poyang Lake in Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The river valley is in the grips of the second worst flooding
since 1954, with water levels in some sections approaching and in
some cases surpassing record highs.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters called on local officials and the general
public as a whole, as well as members of the People's Liberation
Army, armed police and public security units, to do everything
possible to battle the flood and safeguard people's life and
property along the river in line with instructions issued by
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
The circular called on local provinces and cities to introduce
the following measures:
</P>
</TEXT>
