</P>
<P>
The National Fertilizer Agency of Ethiopia said a total of
475,556 tons of fertilizm/ }.C1Uf[g 103,748 tons of fertilizer
in reserve, is being distributed throughout the country, the
Ethiopian Herald reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The fertilizer in distribution is in excess of this year's
planned target by 117,556 tons and this year's supply is
significantly greater than that of last year, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
A sum of 85 million U.S. Dollars obtained from the Ethiopian
government, including foreign loan and aid, has been allocated
for the purchase of the fertilizer, the agency noted.
</P>
<P>
Bumper harvest would be expected in next production season as
the weather has signifAc2nt'\k~.X7ges from June to September.
This is the major agricultural production season which produces
90 percent of the product of the year. 
