<HEADLINE> Circular Urges Priority on Battle Against Yangtze Flooding (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Place top priority on clearly defining responsibilities for
flood prevention and control in order to secure the Yangtze River,
Dongting Lake, Poyang Lake, major cities and reservoirs, and
protect life and property;
</P>
<P>
-- Organize patrols and powerful task forces, eliminate
decision-making mistakes, and spare no effort to protect dikes and
dams;
</P>
<P>
Flood prevention plans should be worked out to properly prepare
for any emergency situation. Party and government officials at
different levels should be held accountable for ensuring the
safety of local people, and take steps to move people from
threatened areas to reduce losses to an absolute minimum;
</P>
<P>
-- Meteorological and hydrological stations should closely
monitor weather forecasts and changing flood conditions in order
to supply accurate information to flood control headquarters at
all levels, and communications departments should ensure smooth
telecommunications operations;
</P>
<P>
-- Efforts should be expanded to strengthen the relief effort,
maintain public order, and ensure proper arrangements for the
daily needs of residents. Efforts should also center on providing
health care, epidemic prevention, rebuilding and restoring
production.
</P>
<P>
The circular urged Party organizations at all levels, Party
members, young people, soldiers, armed police units and public
security departments to play a leading role in battling floods.
</P>
</TEXT>
