<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Chinese Cities Enjoy Good Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The latest report released by the
China Environmental Monitoring Center today indicated that the
country's major cities continued to enjoy good air quality over
the past week.
</P>
<P>
Eleven cities -- Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Haikou, Beihai, Qinhuangdao,
Yantai, Guilin, Nanchang, Zhanjiang, Nanning and Ningbo --
recorded excellent air quality between July 17-23, according to
the report.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six cities, including Shanghai, Chongqing, Tianjin,
Nanjing and Guangzhou, reported good air quality during the period.
</P>
<P>
Nine cities, including Beijing, Xi'an and Hohhot, reported
slight air pollution. Major problems in the Chinese capital
centered on nitrogen oxide levels, with the remaining eight cities
reporting high levels of suspended particles.
</P>
<P>
Experts noted that a major reason for China's good urban air
quality reports over the past four weeks centered on the fact that
the most experienced either clear days or thunderstorms which
purified the air.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
