<HEADLINE> Developing Tourism In Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, port city in northeast
China's Liaoning Province, is trying to upgrade tourism to get it
to contribute 15 percent to the city's GDP by year 2010.
</P>
<P>
It has a series of activities to get local people to be more
civilized and has spent heavily on infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Dalian has a 1,900-km. coastline with beaches, geothermal hot
springs, cultural and historical sites at Daheishan, and a modern
city.
</P>
<P>
It has more than 1,000 travel agencies, 150 of which can help
overseas tourists. The tourism sector has created 130,000 jobs in
the city. Its hotels have more than 70,000 beds.
</P>
<P>
Last year, tourism generated 6.46 billion yuan in earnings,
representing 7.79 percent of the city's GDP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
