<HEADLINE> Capital Airport Operates Normally Despite Runway Damage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Capital International
Airport reported normal operations on Wednesday despite the fact
that heavy rainfall and high temperatures damaged a section of
the west runway.
</P>
<P>
The damaged runway was closed for 24 hours, with the east
runway handling more than 400 flights during the period.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the airport management department noted that the
west runway reopened of yesterday, with the previous day's closure
having no serious effect on operations and a only a few flights
experiencing delays. 
</P>
