<DOCNO> XIE19980724.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Obuchi Elected Japan's LDP President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Foreign Minister Keizo
Obuchi was elected president of Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic
Party (LDP) Friday, beating the two other candidates in the race.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi, 61, polled a majority on the first secret ballot at a
meeting of LDP members of both houses of the Diet (parliament) and
representatives from 47 prefectures.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi is expected to be designated prime minister by the House
of Representatives (lower house) on July 30 to replace Ryutaro
Hashimoto, who announced his resignation on July 13 after the
LDP's devastating defeat in the July 12 House of Councillors
election.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi will serve out the rest of Hashimoto's term until the
end of September next year.
</P>
<P>
The other two candidates in the race were former Chief Cabinet
Secretary Seiroku Kajiyama, 72, and Health and Welfare Minister
Junichiro Koizumi, 56.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi won 225 of the 411 valid votes cast, with Kajiyama
winning 102 and Koizumi 84. There was one invalid vote.
</P>
<P>
A total of 414 LDP members, including 367 LDP Diet members and
47 prefectural representatives of the party's local branches, were
eligible to vote in the race for the party's presidency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
