<HEADLINE> Zou Yulin May Become First Asian To Circle Globe on Foot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Zou Yulin, a resident of Chengdu,
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province, will begin a walk
around the world late this August.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old Zou, who speaks both English and
Japanese, plans to complete his global journey in about
twenty-eight months.
</P>
<P>
He hopes to become the first Asian to circle the globe on foot,
after ending his trip in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Zou will set out from Shenzhen City late next month, and return
to Beijing sometime in 2000, via Hong Kong, Japan, Canada, the
United States, Britain, France, Holland, Germany, Switzerland,
Italy, Austria, Hungary, Romania, Ukraine, Russia and Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Zuo will cover a total of 42,000 kms and will have to walk some
32,000 km overland.
</P>
<P>
In the 1980s, Zou reportedly took twenty-six months to finish a
solo trip following the route taken by the Chinese Workers' and
Peasants' Red Army during their famous "Long March" in 1934-1935.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
