<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Floods, Landslides in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 persons have been
killed and many others injured in floods and landslides brought by
three days of incessant rains near Jayapura, capital of
Indonesia's Irian Jaya Province.
</P>
<P>
The rains that began Tuesday also damaged tens of houses,
schools and other buildings as well as crops, Antara News Agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The disaster killed seven in Serui, capital of Yapen Waropen
district, and the nearby villages.
</P>
<P>
"Floods rose up to one-meter in our school in Barwaikap
village, prompting a temporary halt in school activities," the
report quoted an elementary school teacher as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a landslide in Abepura district caused the collapse
of a crude tunnel being dug by 10 people in search of gold. Five
were killed instantly, four others were pulled out alive, and one
was reported missing. 
</P>
