<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0700 GMT, July 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japanese Foreign Minister Keizo Obuchi was elected
president of the ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) Friday
afternoon in a three-way presidential race.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi, 61, is expected to be designated new Japanese prime
minister by the House of Representatives (lower house) July 30 as
the LDP holds a majority in the powerful lower house of the Diet
(parliament). (Japan-LDP-Voting-Result, URGENT)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)
opened its 31st ministerial meeting here Friday to discuss a
number of issues affecting the region, with Philippine President
Joseph Estrada calling for restoring financial and economic
stability and for a true ASEAN community.
</P>
<P>
Presiding over the opening session, President Estrada called
restoration of financial and economic stability in the region "our
immediate concern." (ASEAN-Ministerial Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini Thursday urged
Albania to show the "maximum of moderation" in the current phase
of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
He made the request while meeting with visiting Albanian
Foreign Minister Paskal Milo, according to an Italian Foreign
Ministry press release. Dini told Milo that the international
community would oppose "with determination" any enlargement of the
Kosovo conflict involving Albanian territory. (Italy-Albania)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- The European Union has hailed the up-coming summit
of the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) in
Colombo later this month as an opportunity to ease tensions in the
region, official Daily News reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The head of delegation of the European Commission here
Ambassador Ilkka Uusitalo Thursday said the summit comes at an
important time for the South Asian region and, if it is to be well
 used, can provide an opportunity for the leaders of the region to
 ease tensions and to take constructive steps in the regional
integration process in South Asia. (SAARC Summit-EU) 
</P>
