<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Tombs In Southern China Prove To Be Mysterious </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- More than a hundred tombs found
recently in Yongning County in south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region contain the remains of humans, some of them
dismembered, that date back more than 5,000 years.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists say that it is strange to find bodies that have
been deliberately dismembered before being buried. The heads of
some were cut off and put into the chest cavity, and arms and legs
were cut off and put at the sides of the tombs.
</P>
<P>
"The tombs represent unique burial customs and are valuable for
the study of pre-historic society and customs in Guangxi and
southeastern Asia," said Fu Xianguo, head of the team that
unearthed the tombs.
</P>
<P>
The 149 tombs have 181 corpses, more than 1,000 relics like
pottery and stone and bone tools. The remains of animals that were
the food of these people were found by the team in a
500-square-meter area in the Dingshi Mountains in Yongning County
last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980724.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Wins Rhythmic All-Around Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Alina Kabayeva won the
rhythmic all-around title in the gymnastics competitions at the
Goodwill Games in Long Island, New York on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
She savored the victory by scoring a total of 39.781 points,
namely 9.941 from rope, 9.941 from hoop, 9.958 from clubs and
9.941 from ribbon.
</P>
<P>
The Russian woman led all the way in the routines at the Nassau
Veterans Memorial Coliseum Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
"Going into the competition, I wasn't sure how I would do, but
after I performed well on the first event (rope), I gained
confidence," Kabayeva said at the post-game press briefing.
</P>
<P>
The Russian woman, who finished first at the European
championships in May, said that it was one of her best
performances.
</P>
<P>
The last gymnastics event also provided the chance for Yelena
Vitrichenko to bag home one more silver medal for Ukraine. She
scored a total of 39.657 points.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, Yevgeniya Pavlina took the last gymnastics bronze
medal for Belarus with a mark of 39.640. 
</P>
</TEXT>
