<HEADLINE> International Drug Rehabilitation Training In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ningbo International Drug
Rehabilitation and Training Center, the first for use by
foreigners in China, has opened in the port city of Ningbo in
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Four medical doctors from Russia, Honduras, Indonesia, and
Singapore have become the first group of students. They will have
half a month of study of a "one plus one" rehabilitation therapy
developed by Yang Guodong, a professor at the Ningbo
Drug Rehabilitation Research Center.
</P>
<P>
The new therapy can help addicts resist the temptation of drugs
in a short period of time without suffering.
</P>
<P>
Since its invention in 1991, The therapy has been used to treat
more than 6,000 Chinese and foreign addicts. The Ningbo Drug
Rehabilitation Research Center has established cooperative
relations with many overseas universities and labs.
</P>
<P>
The Ningbo International Drug Rehabilitation and Training
Center is expected to enroll foreign students. China has 695
compulsory drug rehabilitation centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
