<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Archaeologists Discover Caves Used By Early Man Near Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archaeologists have
discovered four individual caves in Miyun County in Beijing's
suburbs that provide new information for the study of early man.
</P>
<P>
The caves are on the south side of Yunfeng Mountain, several
meters above the surrounding countryside. The biggest is just over
5 meters long, 3 meters wide and 2 meters high, and the smallest,
3 meters long and less than 2 meters wide. All of them have earth
beds, a cooking area, a smoke exhaust tunnel, and a niche for a
lamp.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists are still trying to determine the date of the
caves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
