<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Belarus Win Golds at Games Gymnastics (updated) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Huang Xu awarded China its first
gold medal from the parallel bars and Ivan Ivankov of Belarus
claimed the horizontal bar title in the gymnastics competitions at
the Goddwill Games in Long Island, New York on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Huang, 19, scored 9.725 points, 0.025 point more than second
place finisher Ivan Ivankov of Belarus, who got 9.700, the first
gold medal for China as the Goodwill Games entered its fifth-day
competitions since July 19.
</P>
<P>
Huang was the member of the champions team and fifth all-around
finisher at the 1997 world championships.
</P>
<P>
"I am very happy to win the first medal for the Chinese
Gymnastics team," Huang told a press briefing after the
competitions.
</P>
<P>
But Huang said that he also felt sorry "because at the Goodwill
Games, our team just won one gold medal."
</P>
<P>
Huang was placed fourth in the individual pommel horse on
Tuesday and sixth in the rings on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
His teammate Lu Yufu finished fourth in the horizontal bar and
even lower in other events.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal of the parallel bars went to Russia's Alexei
Bondarenko, who got 9.650 points.
</P>
<P>
In the men's horizontal bar, Ivankov gained his winning score
of 9.725. Ivankov, who won the silver in Wednesday's rings, said
that he felt "great" for his performance.
</P>
<P>
Alexei Nemov of Russia took the silver medal with 9.650 points
while Sergei Fedorchenko bagged home a bronze medal for Kazakhstan
with a mark of 9.525. 
</P>
</TEXT>
