<HEADLINE> Hungarian Air Force MIG-29 Plane Crashes in Stunt Flying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 23 (Xinhua) -- One MIG-29 fighter plane of the
Hungarian air force crashed in a stunt flying on Wednesday,
killing the pilot.
</P>
<P>
The plane downed in the open field near Kecskemet, central
Hungary.
</P>
<P>
The pilot is an outstanding one with 2,000 hours of flight
experience and has flown various kinds of fighter planes, a
defense ministry spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
MIG-29's, the most advanced type of aricraft the Hungary's air
force is equipped with, were imported from Russia in 1993. There
are altogether 28 in the air force.
</P>
<P>
The crash is the first accident for MIG-29's in Hungary, and
the reason is being investigated.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian National Defense Forces has ordered all the
MIG-29's here not to take off until the accident reason is known.
</P>
</TEXT>
