<HEADLINE> Italian FM Urges Albania to Show Moderation in Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini Thursday urged Albania to show the "maximum of moderation" in
the current phase of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
He made the request while meeting with visiting Albanian
Foreign Minister Paskal Milo, according to an Italian Foreign
Ministry press release.
</P>
<P>
Dini told Milo that the international community would oppose
"with determination" any enlargement of the Kosovo conflict
involving Albanian territory.
</P>
<P>
He asked his Albanian counterpart to help find possible talking
partners among the ethnic Albanians in the Serbian province of
Kosovo to address the international community.
</P>
<P>
Before flying back to Tirana, the Albanian foreign minister
told reporters at the airport that Italy and Albania are committed
to following a common strategy to end the fighting.
</P>
<P>
"For both countries, intervention by NATO forces is only to be
sought if all possible negotiations fail," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Italy and Albania believe a peaceful solution is still
possible in Kosovo, " he added.
</P>
<P>
In recent days, clashes between Serbian security forces and
the armed ethnic Albanians in Kosovo have threatened to spill over
into the neighboring country of Albania, and Serbian defense on
Kosovo's frontier with Albania has been beefed up with mine fields
and other measures to halt the alleged entry of armed men from
Albanian territory. Enitem

