<HEADLINE> hke - Vietnam to Push Ahead With National Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is determined to push ahead
with national reforms, the General-Secretary of the Communist
Party of Vietnam Le Kha Phieu said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Party leader was speaking at a meeting here with heads of
diplomatic missions, international organizations and
representatives of foreign companies in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
"In any circumstances, the party, the government and the people
of Vietnam are determined to speed up renovation, make full use of
internal resources, and promote international cooperation," the
party leader stressed.
</P>
<P>
Apart from restructuring state-owned enterprises to boost their
production and competitiveness, Phieu said the government will
readjust investment structure, particularly in those domains that
could bring early results.
</P>
<P>
The party leader said foreign investment is being used
effectively in Vietnam, and the country will continue with its
administrative reform to improve the investment environment.
</P>
<P>
Speaking about the economic situation, Phieu said vietnam has
taken active measures to overcome difficulties caused by the
regional monetary and financial crisis and natural calamities.
