<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka donates 40,000 Eyes to foreign Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 24 (Xinhua)- As of July 21 this year, the Sri
Lankan Eye Donation Society (SLEDS) has gifted 40,010 eyes to
foreign countries since its eye donation service commenced in May
1964, the society's told Xinhua by telephone Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Hudson Silua, president of the SLEDS, said the society sent
a pair of corneas to Loving Blind Association of Taipei on July
21, surpassing 40,010 eyes which had already being sent abroad.
</P>
<P>
Of 62 countries and areas , Pakistan has been the largest
recipient country by over 16,800 followed by Indonesia, India,
Saudi Arabia and Japan, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added the SLEDS had gifted about 10,000 eyes to China
including 6,000 eyes to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Set up in 1961 on his initiative, the SLEDS has received warm
response from the Sri Lankan people. An international eye bank was
launched in 1965 with the support of the health authority in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The first three sets of eyes were sent to Singapore on May 25,
1964. since then an average 1,334 eyes have been sent to foreign
countries annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
