<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 23 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary General Kofi
Annan ended his five-nation Latin American tour and left here
Thursday for the U.N. headquarters in New York.
</P>
<P>
In his first Latin American tour, Annan met separately with
heads of state of Brazil, Uruguay, Argentina, Guatemala and
Mexico. He exchanged views with them on topics of Latin American
peace and democratization, social and economic
development, international efforts against drugs as well as U.N.
structural reform and peacekeeping operations.
