<HEADLINE> 30 People Missing in Boat Capsize in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Thirty people were missing after a
ferry boat capsized Thursday in Kangsa river in northern
Bangladesh's Mymensingh district, a media report here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The deck of the mechanized boat, which was overloaded with
passengers, cracked in the middle of the river at Hahishakanda,
witnesses were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Of some 50 passengers on board, 20 managed to swim ashore while
30 others were still missing.
</P>
<P>
The boat was salvaged by local people and the search for the
missing victims were continuing, the report said. 
