<HEADLINE> China, Belarus Win Golds at Goodwill Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 23 (Xinhua) -- China's Huang Xu won the parallel
bars and Ivan Ivankov of Belarus claimed the horizontal bar title
in the gymnastics competitions at the Goodwill Games in Long
Island, New York on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Huang, 19, scored 9.725 points, 0.025 point more than the
second place finisher Ivan Ivankov of Belarus, who got 9.700.
</P>
<P>
Huang, member of the champions team and fifth all-around
finisher at the 1997 world championships, won the first gold medal
for China in the gymnastics events since the Games started on July
19.
</P>
<P>
He was placed fourth in the individual pommel horse on Tuesday
and sixth in the rings event on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal of the parallel bars went to Russia's Alexei
Bondarenko, who got 9.650 points.
</P>
<P>
In the men's horizontal bar on Thursday, Ivankov who won the
silver in the rings event on wednesday, gained a winning score of
9.725.
</P>
<P>
Alexei Nemov of Russia took the silver medal in the horizontal
bar with 9.650 points while Sergei Fedorchenko bagged a bronze
medal for Kazakhstan with a mark of 9.525.
</P>
<P>
Another Chinese gymnast Lu Yufu finished fourth with 9.475
points. 
</P>
