<HEADLINE> EU Hails SAARC As Opportunity To Ease Tensions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union has hailed the
up-coming summit of the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation (SAARC) in Colombo later this month as an opportunity
to ease tensions in the region, official Daily News reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The head of delegation of the European Commission here
Ambassador Ilkka Uusitalo Thursday said the summit comes at an
important time for the South Asian region and, if it is to be well
used, can provide an opportunity for the leaders of the region to
ease tensions and to take constructive steps in the regional
integration process in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC charter does not allow bilateral matters to be taken
up at summit but they can be discussed informally on the sidelines
of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of India and Pakistan are expected to meet on the
sidelines of the SAARC summit to discuss ways of breaking the
deadlock in their talks due to various differences including the
Kashmir issue. Relations of The two nations have become more tense
following their nuclear tests in May this year.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador pointed out that the European Union supports the
efforts of the South Asian countries to strengthen their regional
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Though we are not suggesting any specific form or model for
such cooperation, in general terms we consider that such a
cooperation, the same way as it has been in Europe, would be
beneficial also for the countries and people in the South Asian
region", the newspaper quoted the ambassador as saying.
</P>
<P>
The coming year may also provide an opportunity to forge closer
links with the EU and the SAARC, said the ambassador, adding that
there is already a memorandum of understanding between the
European Commission and the SAARC secretariat and both would hope
that concrete actions could be taken based on that memorandum.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
