<HEADLINE> Hungary to Help Ethnic Hungarians in Yugoslav Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian Minister of Foreign
Affairs Martonyi Sanos Thursday said here Hungary will try to
help the ethnic Hungarians in the Yugoslav army out of the armed
conflicts in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with ethnic Hungarian leaders from Vojvodina province
of Yugoslavia, Martonyi said, it is worrisome that hundreds of
ethnic Hungarian soldiers in the Yugoslav army have been sent to
Kosovo and died there.
</P>
<P>
Hungary will work to help those reluctant soldiers in the
Kosovo conflict return to their homes, he said.
</P>
<P>
Observers here say protection of Hungarians living outside
Hungary is traditionally a high priority in Hungarian foreign
policy. And there are about 5 million, one-third of a total of 15
million Hungarians, living overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
