<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India:
</P>
<P>
-- The Clifton Administration has asked 7 Indian scientists to
leave the United States and 75 others working in U.S. laboratories
are also likely to be forced out.
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The Central Bureau of Investigation seized more than 8 kgs
of uranium and 31 gram platinum piece, and arrested 3 people
Wednesday in Chennal, in the southern state of Tamil Nadu.
</P>
<P>
The Statesman:
</P>
<P>
-- Delhi High Court expressed concern at the state of
lawlessness, which has gripped the city in the last couple of
months with a spate of robberies and dacoities committed in broad
daylight.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Times:
</P>
<P>
-- India has set up an 8-member Cabinet Committee on Foreign
Trade head by Vajpayee to review the poor performance of exports
and the steps to achieve the target of 20 percent of annual
growth. 
