<HEADLINE> Urgent: 31st ASEAN Ministerial Meeting Opens in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The 31st Ministerial Meeting of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) opened here Friday.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day event, foreign ministers from the nine ASEAN
member countries will discuss the ongoing Asian financial crisis,
the forthcoming Cambodian elections, nuclear proliferation in
South Asia, regional cooperation against transnational crimes and
other important issues.
</P>
<P>
The ministers are also expected to decide whether there will be
a change in ASEAN's policy from "non-interference" to "flexible
engagement." However, the proposal is opposed by most ASEAN member
countries. 
</P>
