<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Growth In China's Foreign Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- China made considerable progress
in arranging foreign government loans and financing in the first
half of this year, according to Hu Zhaoqing, a Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Hu told a press conference today that Japan, Germany, and 20
other countries have pledged loans to China and that 792 million
U.S. dollars of loans have been put to use in 43 projects.
</P>
<P>
China has also had some encouraging results from changes in its
foreign aid program, he said. During the six-month period, 5.6
billion U.S. dollars worth of new contracts were signed for labor
services, project design, and consultation and 4 billion dollars
worth of business was done, a 15.9 percent increase, he said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, 323,900 Chinese were working overseas under
these contracts, an increase of 36,000 people. Foreign aid and
international projects and labor services are playing a
significant role in increasing exports of equipment and goods, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
