<HEADLINE> U.S. Names NBA Dreamers for Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The United States has named its
squad for the World Basketball Championship in Greece next month,
but none of the NBA big names was included in the roster.
</P>
<P>
As the previous NBA Dream Teams always won the gold medal with
ease, the current team of NBA dreamers face tough challenges from
their European counterparts.
</P>
<P>
"With this team you're playing to win and nobody expects us to
win," said coach Rudy Tomjanovich.
</P>
<P>
Tomjanovich has reduced his squad from 15 members to 12 on
Thursday and would play their last exhibition game on Saturday
against Italy before proceeding from Rome to Greece on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The new squad of no-names was triggered off by the labor
dispute between NBA stars and the league, and will rely on their
moves on offence and pressure on defence to exploit their
athleticism, said the coach.
</P>
<P>
However, Tomjanovich, coach of two-time NBA champion Houston
Rockets, declined to name his five starters and intended to use
all 12 players as "all these guys are pretty close in talent."
</P>
</TEXT>
