<HEADLINE> China's Technology Exports Continue to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- China's technology exports were on
the increase during the first six months of the year, Hu Zhaoqing,
spokesman for the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Co-operation, said this morning.
</P>
<P>
China had signed 808 contracts on import and export of
technology, valued at 5.78 billion U.S. dollars by the end of
June, according to the spokesman, who released the figure at a
press conference to give an overview of the country's foreign
trade and economic cooperation in the first half of 1998.
</P>
<P>
"These include 398 import contracts valued at 3.24 billion
U.S. dollars and 410 export contracts valued at 2.54 billion
U.S. dollars," Hu said.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the decrease in the number of export contracts, their
value shot up by 43.5 per cent.The average contract value
increased from 2.386 million to 6.195 million U.S. dollars," Hu
added. "Imports ran the other way with a 13.7 percent increase in
the number of contracts and a 16 percent decrease in the total
value." 
</P>
</TEXT>
