<HEADLINE> Chang Wins over Damm in Legg Mason Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Michael Chang won his third
round game on Thursday, crusing to his 14th straight victory at
the FitzGerald Tennis Center in the Legg Mason Tennis Classic.
</P>
<P>
The top-seeded Chang, two-time defending champion, recorded a 6-4, 6-1 win
over Martin Damm of the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Chang led Damm 5-4 in the first set when their match was
delayed for more than an hour by rain. Chang broke Damm's service
after the delay to win the first set and then cruised to victory
in the second set.
</P>
<P>
Also advancing to the quarterfinals were third-seed Wayne
Ferreira of South Africa, fifth-seed Filip DeWulf of Belgium and
14th-seed Scott Draper of Australia.
</P>
<P>
Draper beat fourth-seed Byron Black of Zimbabwe 6-2, 6-4.
Earlier in the second round, left-hander Draper also eliminated
Byron's brother, Wayne, out of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Ferreira who stopped the comeback of Jimmy Arias on Tuesday,
sealed off his Wednesday's game against qualifier David Caldwell
7-5, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Andre Agassi and Jim Courier were scheduled to play third-round
matches later Thursday night. 
