<HEADLINE> Northwest China Region Enjoys Booming Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region recorded handled foreign trade worth 178 million
US dollars during the first half of this year, up 62.4 percent on
the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
The total included a 25.6 percent rise in exports to 130
million US dollars compared to the 1997 period, and a dramatic 720
percent jump in imports to 50 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The region currently grants preferential policies for export
quotas and technology upgrades to profitable enterprises with
export rights.
</P>
<P>
Local enterprises reported a 151 percent growth in exports
during the first half of the year compared to the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
The region exerted great efforts to restructure the structure
of export commodities and develop new markets in the Middle East,
in addition to increasing exports to traditional markets in the
Americas and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Europe jumped by 200 percent during the six month
period, with the export volume to United States growing by 34
percent and to Japan by 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The export volume for each of 11 general products surpassed
five million US dollars, with related products accounting for 62.3
percent of local exports during the January-June period.
</P>
<P>
The foreign trade volume for enterprises engaged in processing
with imported raw materials exceeded 43 million US dollars during
the period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
