<HEADLINE> Private Sector Providing Jobs In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The private sector of Shanghai,
China's major economic power house, has provided jobs for
152,000 workers who were laid off at state-owned enterprises over
the past three years.
</P>
<P>
This is seen as something that is very helpful for reforms of
state companies and for social stability.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai now has one of the strongest private sectors in China,
with over 60,000 individually-owned companies (employing fewer
than 8 people) and 156,000 private enterprises (employing 8 or
more).
</P>
<P>
The sector may become an important place for unemployed people
to find work because of new government policies allowing people
who have been laid off to open private businesses and because of
tax cuts. 
