<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea, China Win in Baseball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 23 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and China both won their
games in the Baseball World Championships by beating United States
and Spain respectively on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kyung Hun-Ho and Kim Byung Hyun combined for 14 strikeouts as
South Korea beat the United States 3-1 while China rolled over
Spain 9-2 at Florence.
</P>
<P>
With two straight wins, South Korea shared the top spot in Pool
A with the Netherlands and Australia as the latters routed their opponents in
earlier games at Palermo.
</P>
<P>
The United States tailed in Pool A with two losses and faces an
uphill battle to reach the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean hurlers were dominant, allowing only one
extra-base hit, a double in the seventh inning by Brad Cresse, who
came around to score the Americans' run on a single by catcher
Joshua Bard.
</P>
<P>
Kyung was pulled after allowing the run with none out. Kim came
on to end the rally and pick up the save with three innings of
no-hit pitching for South Korea, which lost to Cuba in the 1994
title game.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands, which beat the United States 3-1 Wednesday,
got another strong pitching performance and eight members of the
starting lineup got at least one hit in a 12-1 rout of first-time
entrant Russia that also lost two games.
</P>
<P>
Australia beat Nicaragua 9-2 with Paul Gonzales had three hits,
including a run-scoring double and a three-run homer. Nicaragua
fell to 1-1.
</P>
<P>
In the other Pool A game of the day, Canada edged winless
Chinese Taipei 5-4 for one win against one loss at Messina, Sicily.
</P>
<P>
In Pool B, five-time defending champion Cuba cruised to a 14-1
victory over South Africa at Vicenza, Japan beat Italy 10-3 at
Parma, the Dominican Republic defeated Panama 9-3 at Rimini, and
China beat Spain 9-2 at Florence.
</P>
<P>
Cuba, the Dominican Republic and Japan share the group lead
with 2-0 records.
</P>
<P>
The top four teams from each group advance to next week's
quarterfinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
