<HEADLINE> Floyd Named Director of Bulls' Basketball Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chicago Bulls has named Tim
Floyd its director of basketball operations on Thursday, instead
of head coach for the moment.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls chairman Jerry Reinsdorf said that Floyd has joined
the team as a director with the head coaching job remains open
until an NBA labor dispute is resolved.
</P>
<P>
"We are leaving open for Phil (Jackson), Michael (Jordan) and
Scottie (Pippen) to return and defend their championship, while at
the same time providing a plan to move forward if they chose not
to do so," Reinsdorf said.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Jackson is unlikely to return to his coaching job in the
Bulls as he said at the beginning of last season that "it would
take wild horses to drag me back" for another season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
