<HEADLINE> Beijing's Trade With Taiwan Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Beijing and Taiwan
has been on the increase since 1995, according to Beijing Customs.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show trade with Taiwan worth 27.17 million
U.S. dollars in the first half of the year, four times the figure
for the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Goods brought in from Taiwan accounted for 10.49 million
dollars, or 2.2 times last year's figure and goods supplied to
Taiwan were worth 16.68 million US dollars, 8.5 times last year's
figure.
</P>
<P>
Trade with Taiwan has an increasing amount of processed goods
and investment from Taiwan businessmen, and trade by
overseas-funded enterprises accounts for the major part.
</P>
</TEXT>
