<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Urban Wholesale Market Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Thursday
approved a loan of some 15.9 million U.S. dollars equivalent for
the Wholesale Market Project I in Poland.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be utilized to assist in the construction of a
commercially self-sustaining urban wholesale market for the
Gdansk-Gdynia-Sopot metropolitan area.
</P>
<P>
This project will facilitate the development of a business
partnership between public entity shareholders and private sector
investors.
</P>
<P>
The borrower, the Pomorskie Hurtowe Centrum Rolno-Spozywcze
S.A., and its shareholders, have demonstrated their commitment by
securing and contributing required equity financing for the
investment.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, when Poland resumed borrowing from the World Bank,
Bank commitments to the country have totalled 4.7 billion dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
